Is the švarc system "prohibited or allowed?
The law must be regulated in some way and, if it prohibits anything, then not even the Prime Minister of the government can prevent the action of the Office which has the obligation to carry out such controls and to demand obligations.
You can say, "We change the law and allow it," but you can't say we'll do anything.
In the law on public procurement, the rules are quite strict as to how to act formally, and that is how it should be to protect public competition.
But on the other hand, it is tragic that the candidate with the best offer is excluded because he does not meet the formal requirements.
The law will never be perfect, but its application must be correct.
