To do this, you have to go down every day to the bottom of your crater, where the sulfurous gas that emanates from the bowels of the Earth solidifies when you come into contact with the air.
After uprooting large sulfur rocks, which in total weigh about 70 kilos, it carries them in two baskets of bamboo that carry on their shoulders through steep stone paths.
It is only 250 meters to the top of the volcano, which rises to 2,386 meters of altitude, but the exhausted carriers take more than 40 minutes to ascend by tortoise, keeping the balance and strenuous measuring their steps so as not to slip and fall down the cliff.
